<book title="Darai's SpaceRace - the Guide">
	<include ref="gbook:xml/standard.xml" />

	<chapter id="ch0">
		<page id="pg0">
			<title>Welcome Player</title>
			<p>This book you have in your hand is here for you. To make your life easier and give it some direction.</p>
			<p />
			<p>If you prefer Quest based guide it is also part of this modpack. You can use the Better Questing Shortcut or open the Quest Book.</p> 
			<p />
			<p align="center">good luck, Darai</p> 
		</page>
		<page id="pg1">
			<p bold="true" italics="true">Links</p>
			<p>There are some very important points you should know:</p>
			<link ref="ch1">Just Quests?</link>
			<link ref="ch2">Sudden Deaths</link>
			<link ref="ch3">Wrong Recipes</link>
			<link ref="ch4">Finding Resources</link>
		</page>
		<page id="pg2">
			<p bold="true" italics="true">The Goal</p>
			<p>To complete this modpack (if you need a final task for a sandbox game) you must build your spaceship and reach the orbit of the Mooshroom Moon.</p>
			<p />
			<p>Next to it is a small moon called Haven. Terraform it and build there a monument of your success.</p>			
		</page>
		<page id="pg3">
			<p>For the monument, use at least following resources:</p>
			<stack item="taiga:violium_block" count="1000" x="0"/>
			<stack item="taiga:astrium_block" count="1000" x="40"/>
			<stack item="draconicevolution:draconic_block" count="1000" y="40"/>
			<stack item="tconstruct:materials"  meta="50" count="1" x="40" y="40"/>
			<space height="60" />
			<p>Optionally you can prove yourself by crafting the most expensive thing in this modpack:</p>
			<stack item="storagedrawers:upgradeCreative" meta="1" x="0"/>
		</page>
	</chapter>
	<chapter id="ch1">
		<page id="pg0">
			<title>Why not just Quests?</title>
			<p>You can easily get lost in quests. So, the most important topics are available also here.</p>
			<p />
			<p>Also some people despite quests all together and I want this to be fun also for them.</p>
		</page>
		<page id="pg1">
			<p>The most important chapters like "Where to look for resources" or "What can kill you" are also described in the Quest Book.</p>
			<p />
			<p>Wrong Recipes not so much...</p>
			<p>Also It is much easier to write this guidebook, so it will be completed in version one of the modpack and the Quest Book will not.</p>
		</page>
	</chapter>
	<chapter id="ch2">
		<page id="pg0">
			<title>Dumb ways to Die</title>
			<p>There are few things in this pack which can easily and quickly kill you. Or at least kill your mood.</p>
			<p />
			<p>Some people do not like this so here is all the warnings I could think of.</p>
		</page>
		<page>
			<link ref="ch2:d0">Aqua Creepers</link>
			<link ref="ch2:d1">Spice of Life</link>
			<link ref="ch2:d1a">Moving World</link>
			<link ref="ch2:d2">Void</link>
			<link ref="ch2:d3">Portals</link>
			<link ref="ch2:d4">Monsters</link>
			<link ref="ch2:d5">Warp</link>
		</page>
		<page id="d0">
			<p bold="true" italics="true">Aqua Creepers</p>
			<p>Deadly fast and living in all Homeworld oceans.</p>
			<p />
			<p>Beware, they can jump from the water if you stand too close.</p>
		</page>
		<page id="d1">
			<p bold="true" italics="true">Spice of Life</p>
			<p>Keep your food list rich. Everything you eat will loose it's effectiveness very quickly.</p>
			<stack item="minecraft:fish" x="0"/>
		</page>
		<page id="d1a">
			<p bold="true" italics="true">Moving the World</p>
			<p>Big part of this modpack is Davinci's Vessels which allows you to turn some blocks into ship/airship and fly them.</p>
			<stack item="davincisvessels:marker" x="0"/>
			<space height="20" />
			<p>Beware, even though this mod is great, it can crash the game. Play it safe and make yourself accustomed to this mod first.</p>
		</page>
		<page />
		<page id="d2">
			<p bold="true" italics="true">Falling into Void</p>
			<p>Some places are dangerous to land in. Namely Asteroid Worlds, The End Ocean and Lava Worlds.</p>
			<p></p>
			<p>On all those places, you can easily loose your rocket on landing attempt with everything on-board. Be prepared for it and have all the spare parts in your pocket.</p>
		</page>
		<page>
			<link ref="ch5:pg1">Asteroid Belt</link>
			<link ref="ch5:pg2">Lava World</link>
			<link ref="ch5:pg6">The End</link>
			<link ref="ch5:pg8">Ocean World</link>
			<link ref="ch5:pg9">Rocks In Sky</link>
		</page>
		<page id="d3">
			<p bold="true" italics="true">Portals</p>
			<p>All portals are locked by default. To unlock them, you have to:</p>
			<p></p>
			<p>Craft a specific ITEM, make the portal out of the correct BLOCK and activate it with the correct IGNITER.</p>
		</page>
		<page>
			<p>Item, Block and Igniter:</p>
			<p>For UnderEnd:</p>
			<stack item="immersiveengineering:faradaySuit_chest" x="0"/>
			<stack item="tp:reinforced_glass" x="20"/>
			<stack item="tp:golden_scythe" x="40"/>
			<space height="20" />
			<p>For The Nether:</p>
			<stack item="mysticalagriculture:uranium_seeds" x="0"/>
			<stack item="minecraft:obsidian" x="20"/>
			<stack item="minecraft:flint_and_steel" x="40"/>
			<space height="20" />
			<p>For The End is enough to unlock it. To get there use a rocket, it is a moon orbiting the Blue Gas Giant.</p>
			<stack item="draconicevolution:draconium_ingot" x="0"/>
		</page>
		<page id="d4">
			<p bold="true" italics="true">Monsters</p>
			<p>To make the game more fun I tweaked the monsters a little bit. And to make it even more fun, I tweaked them differently on every planet.</p>
			<p></p>
			<p>So, don't be that much surprised, ok?</p>
		</page>
		<page />
		<page id="d5">
			<p bold="true" italics="true">Warp</p>
			<p>I will not explain to you how a warp engine works. But there is one thing specific in this pack.</p>
			<p></p>
			<p>You need to put into the Warp Controller the correct World Orb, before you will be allowed to warp.</p>
			<p></p>
			<p>Every planet has it's own orb, with consistent-ish name.</p>
		</page>
		<page>
			<p>Not like moons, once you are orbiting a planet you can use rocket to get to any moon it has.</p>
			<p></p>
			<p>As it is now, to get to every next planet, you need to find resources, which are specific to the previous planet, first. This is the correct sequence of World Orbs:</p>
			<stack item="bqmie:icon_item" meta="16" x="0"/>
			<stack item="bqmie:icon_item" meta="14" x="20"/>
			<stack item="bqmie:icon_item" meta="17" x="40"/>
			<stack item="bqmie:icon_item" meta="13" x="60"/>
			<stack item="bqmie:icon_item" meta="15" x="80"/>
			<stack item="bqmie:icon_item" meta="18" x="10" y="20"/>
			<stack item="bqmie:icon_item" meta="22" x="30" y="20"/>
		</page>
	</chapter>
	<chapter id="ch3">
		<page id="pg0">
			<title>Messed-up Recipes</title>
			<p>If you don't know... I changed A LOT of recipes. JEI caught most of the changes but as I understand not all of them.</p>
			<p />
			<p>So about some things, it will be telling you that such receipt exists and it will not work.</p>
		</page>
		<page id="pg1">
			<p>Here is the list of what is the JEI lying about:</p>
			<link ref="ch3:pg2">Charcoal</link>
			<link ref="ch3:pg3">Smelting</link>
			<link ref="ch3:pg4">Refined Storage</link>
			<link ref="ch3:pg5">Nihilite Alloy</link>
		</page>
		<page id="pg2">
			<p bold="true" italics="true">Charcoal</p>
			<p>Forget burning logs in a furnace. Charcoal can be now made only in the Forestry Charcoal Pit.</p>
			<p />
			<p>For those who don't know what that is, you build a pyramid of Loam with Piled Wood in it, light it up and wait.</p>
			<stack item="forestry:pile_dirt" x="0"/>
			<stack item="forestry:pile_wood" x="20"/>
			<stack item="minecraft:flint_and_steel" x="40"/>
		</page>
		<page>		
			<p>Also Charcoal is now the only fuel source for making Coal Coke and ultimately burn Iron to Steel.</p>
		</page>
		<page id="pg3">
			<p bold="true" italics="true">Smelting</p>
			<p>I removed smelting of all Sharpening Kits. Since I tweaked their recipes I put it in as the proper fix.</p>
            <small_recipe>
                <stack item="tconstruct:sharpening_kit"/>
                <stack item="railcraft:nugget"/>
                <space />
                <space />
                <stack item="tconstruct:sharpening_kit"/>
            </small_recipe>
		</page>
		<page />
		<page id="pg4">
			<p bold="true" italics="true">RS Solderer</p>
			<p>Refined Storage Solderer recipes are completely wrong. JEI just gives the original list without my changes. So here is what is different:</p>
			<stack item="refinedstorage:processor" meta="6" x="0"/>
			<stack item="refinedstorage:processor" meta="0" x="20"/>
			<stack item="refinedstorage:processor" meta="1" x="40"/>
			<stack item="refinedstorage:processor" meta="2" x="60"/>
			<space height="20" />
			<p>And now the new and better recipes:</p>
			<stack item="refinedstorage:solderer" x="40" y="0"/>
            <small_recipe>
                <stack item="advancedrocketry:wafer"/>
                <stack item="refinedstorage:silicon"/>
                <stack item="actuallyadditions:itemDust" meta="7"/>
                <space />
                <stack item="refinedstorage:processor" meta="6"/>
            </small_recipe>
		</page>
		<page>
			<stack item="refinedstorage:solderer" x="40" y="0"/>
            <small_recipe>
                <stack item="opencomputers:material" meta="12"/>
                <stack item="actuallyadditions:itemCrystalEmpowered" meta="0"/>
                <stack item="actuallyadditions:itemDust" meta="7"/>
                <space />
                <stack item="refinedstorage:processor" meta="0"/>
            </small_recipe>
			<stack item="refinedstorage:solderer" x="40" y="0"/>
            <small_recipe>
                <stack item="opencomputers:material" meta="12"/>
                <stack item="actuallyadditions:itemCrystalEmpowered" meta="3"/>
                <stack item="taiga:uru_dust"/>
                <space />
                <stack item="refinedstorage:processor" meta="1"/>
            </small_recipe>
			<stack item="refinedstorage:solderer" x="40" y="0"/>
            <small_recipe>
                <stack item="opencomputers:material" meta="12"/>
                <stack item="actuallyadditions:itemCrystalEmpowered" meta="2"/>
                <stack item="taiga:yrdeen_dust"/>
                <space />
                <stack item="refinedstorage:processor" meta="2"/>
            </small_recipe>
		</page>
		<page id="pg5">
			<p bold="true" italics="true">Nihilite Alloy</p>
			<p>Nihilite can be alloyed only in the Chemical Reactor now.</p>
			<p />
			<p>Nihilite Ingots and Blocks can be made in Alloy Smelter or from the fluid Nihilite alloy in the casting basin. But they cannot be re-melted to obtain the alloy fluid back.</p>
			<stack item="taiga:nihilite_dust" x="0"/>
			<stack item="taiga:nihilite_ingot" x="20"/>
			<stack item="taiga:nihilite_block" x="40"/>
		</page>
	</chapter>
